text: Fast-food restaurant - Wikipedia Jump to content Search Search Fast-food restaurant 35 languages العربية تۆرکجه Banjar Čeština Dansk Deutsch Eesti Español Esperanto فارسی Français 한국어 Հայերեն Bahasa Indonesia Jawa Ikinyarwanda Magyar Bahasa Melayu မြန်မာဘာသာ Nederlands 日本語 Norsk bokmål Português Русский Simple English کوردی Српски / srpski Suomi Türkçe Українська Tiếng Việt 文言 粵語 中文 Betawi Edit links From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia Type of restaurant A fast-food restaurant in the port of Malinska , Croatia A Hesburger fast-food restaurant in Tapiola , Espoo , Finland A McDonald's restaurant in New York City A Café de Coral restaurant in Hong Kong A fish and chip shop in Broadstairs , England A fast-food restaurant , also known as a quick-service restaurant ( QSR ) within the industry, is a specific type of restaurant that serves fast-food cuisine and has minimal table service . The food served in fast-food restaurants is typically part of a " meat-sweet diet ", offered from a limited menu, cooked in bulk in advance and kept hot, finished and packaged to order, and usually available for take away , though seating may be provided. Fast-food restaurants are typically part of a restaurant chain or franchise operation that provides standardized ingredients and/or partially prepared foods and supplies to each restaurant through controlled supply channels. The term "fast food" was recognized in a dictionary by Merriam–Webster in 1951. [ 1 ] While the first fast-food restaurant in the United States was a White Castle in 1921, [ 2 ] fast-food restaurants had been operating elsewhere much earlier, such as the Japanese fast food company Yoshinoya , started in Tokyo in 1899. [ 3 ] Today, American-founded fast-food chains such as McDonald's ( est. 1940) and KFC (est. 1952) [ 4 ] [ 5 ] [ 6 ] [ 7 ] are multinational corporations with outlets across the globe. Variations on the fast-food restaurant concept include fast-casual restaurants and catering trucks . Fast-casual restaurants have higher sit-in ratios, offering a hybrid between counter-service typical at fast-food restaurants and a traditional table service restaurant. Catering trucks (also called food trucks) often park just outside worksites and are popular with factory workers. title: Last Dublin sighting, sister's 'sinister' fear & 'people of interest'...major Anthony Hanlon 'suspicious' case latest
text: Last Dublin sighting, sister's 'sinister' fear & 'people of interest'...major Anthony Hanlon 'suspicious' case latest The Irish Sun Irish Sun UK Edition US Edition Scottish Sun Search Search Sign in My Account Sun Club Exclusive News Irish News MILESTONE NEARING Last Dublin sighting, sister’s ‘sinister’ fear & ‘people of interest’…major Anthony Hanlon ‘suspicious’ case latest It’s also understood cops have also identified 'people of interest' in the case Stephen Breen , Irish Sun Crime Editor Published: 21:00, 12 Nov 2025 Click to share on Twitter (Opens in new window) Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window) GARDAI are now treating the case of missing man Anthony Hanlon as “suspicious”, it has emerged. The 39-year-old’s sister Jessica was told last week that a Senior Investigating Officer has now been appointed to investigate the case. Advertisement 7 Anthony Hanlon has been missing since last December 7 His sister Jessica fears ‘something sinister’ happened to him 7 CCTV footage captured Anthony’s last known movements Although a number of extensive searches were undertaken in the Drogheda area in Louth and also in Dublin, gardai have been unable to locate him. The search focused on the capital after it emerged he was seen at the PTSB on O’Connell Street. But gardai later established that he had then boarded a bus on the same day. Anthony was last seen alive boarding the Expressway bus in Dublin to Drogheda on December 3. An incident room relating to his disappearance has now been established in Drogheda Garda station. It’s also understood they have identified “people of interest” in the case. Detectives will also re-interview everyone who has provided statements on the case. Advertisement And as the first anniversary of his disappearance approaches, his sister has told of her torment . She said: “It’s almost a year now and we still don’t have any answers. “I have said from day one that I think something sinister has happened to him and I welcome the appointment of a senior investigating officer. “We can’t go through another year of this hell and we just need someone to come forward. 7 Extensive searches were carried out in both Dublin city centre and in Drogheda 7 The first anniversary of Anthony’s disappearance is fast approaching 7 Anthony was last seen boarding an Expressway bus in Dublin “He would never have left so long without contacting us and there must be people out there with information. “The fact it is now being treated as suspicious has confirmed our fears and we just want to know what happened.” We also understand Gardai are following two complex lines of inquiry in the case. Advertisement They are that he fell into the Boyne river or may have been harmed. Officers have also followed an additional 15 lines of inquiry and taken 20 statements.
